			<!-- Begin News/Information Section -->
				<table border="0" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" ID="Table23">
					<tr id="trmasthead">
						<td valign="middle" class="main_font" align="center">
							<font size="3"><b>&nbsp;</b></font>
					    </td>
					</tr>
					
					   <td>

			
			
			



<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2"><b>Site Update</b> - Problems With Pop-up Banners</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=382033" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <blockquote>
  <p>Thanks to some concerned users we are aware of some pop-up banners that are
  acting a little strange. Normally if a pop-banner is closed that is the end of
  it. What some viewers are reporting are popup banners that spawn more banners
  when they are closed. If this occurs, users need to email us immediately so we
  can contact our advertising company to fix the problem.</p>
  <p>Although multi-browser spawns are rather annoying it is important for users
  to note that the above does not apply if you in click on the advertisement in
  any way except to close it. If an advertisement is clicked, you close the
  original browser, and as a result multiple browsers open, we can't change that
  but, if you attempt to close an advertisement directly after it opens without
  ever clicking on it and, more browser open, then you need to <a href="Default.asp?mode=11">contact
  us</a> so we can take care of it.</p>
  <p>Thanks for your help and understanding as we navigate new waters.</p>
</blockquote>

		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
		     <td valign="top">
		     <br><font face="Verdana" size="2"><b><a href="UserUpdate.asp?id=382033">[Add Comments] Please Add your comments here!</a></b></font><br><hr>
			  </td>
		</tr>

		</table>

	</td>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
</tr>
</table>



