			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Hmm, I've been watching the reaction to the pop-ups and the Lore Networks attempt to provide a way around them.  I have to say that it seems like they are doing everything they can to provide an alternative to pop-ups. As for &quot;no pop up boy&quot;, I'm not so sure you understand how this works. Sure, the internet is a free forum for communication. Assuming you have all the equipment, you can put your site up and communicate all you want. The problem is, when you have to start paying for human beings to do site updates and paying for equipment (whether you own it or you are going through a provider) to handle all the traffic that a network like this generates. If these guys don't find some way to make a little money, then all the helpful info you find here everyday will come to a screeching halt. Hate to break it to ya bud, but Everlore provides a service. Just about every other service you find, you will have to pay for. So far they have kept it free (not free for them, mind you. They still had to pay the bills. Only free to us.). Now it's time to decide if the service is worth putting up with a little advertising or paying a few bucks a year. Personally, I'd like to thank Everlore for doing a good job and trying to give us options.
				</font>
